      • initializeConfiguration

        public boolean initializeConfiguration()
                                throws BrickIsNotReadyException
        Talks to the Brick - tells how the motor and sensor port configuration looks like. The brick will then start to initialize its motors and sensors and also creates proper endpoints to connect those with the phone. Waits until the sensor and motor endpoints are coneected to the brick and the sensors received their first SensorEvent-Msg. If an error during the initialization process on the brick occurs. All sensor and motor endpoints on API-Side will be closed and removed and the process will be aborted and has to be restarted. Process times out after INITIALIZATION_TIMEOUT.
        Specified by:
        initializeConfiguration in interface IRobotConfigurator
        Returns:
        true - if initialization was successful
        Throws:
        BrickIsNotReadyException - - when the brick is not connected or ready to receive configuration information
